### Mathematics and Infinity

In mathematics, infinity is a concept that extends beyond the finite. It can be seen in the realm of numbers, where we have different types of infinity. For instance, the set of natural numbers (1, 2, 3, ...) is infinite, but the set of real numbers (which includes all rational and irrational numbers) is even more infinite. This is because the real numbers are uncountably infinite, meaning there is no way to list them all in a sequence.

